  "title": "Preschool English Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role</strong></p><p>MapleBear is seeking an experienced and passionate Preschool English Teacher to join our early childhood team. The successful candidate will be responsible for planning and delivering engaging, age-appropriate English lessons that support children’s language development, confidence, and love for learning in a warm and nurturing preschool environment.</p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Plan, prepare, and deliver high-quality English lessons aligned with MapleBear’s curriculum and ECDA guidelines.</li><li>Create a warm, positive, and stimulating classroom environment that supports active learning and social-emotional development.</li><li>Design and implement age-appropriate teaching materials and activities to develop literacy, communication, and critical thinking skills.</li><li>Use storytelling, songs, role play, games, and hands-on activities to make learning meaningful and engaging.</li><li>Observe, document, and assess children’s progress, providing regular feedback to parents and the teaching team.</li><li>Collaborate closely with colleagues to support the holistic development of every child.</li><li>Maintain classroom safety, routines, and hygiene standards in compliance with ECDA regulations and centre policies.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>At least 5 years of experience working in an early childhood or preschool setting.</li><li>L2 Certification</li><li>Strong proficiency in English, with excellent verbal and written communication skills.</li><li>A genuine passion for early childhood education and nurturing young learners.</li><li>Patient, creative, and energetic, with the ability to adapt teaching approaches to different learning needs.</li><li>Strong classroom management skills and the ability to work collaboratively in a team environment.</li></ul><p><strong>Why Join MapleBear</strong></p><ul><li>Be part of a globally recognised early childhood brand</li><li>Supportive and collaborative school culture</li><li>Opportunities to contribute meaningfully to curriculum delivery and classroom practice</li><li>Make a lasting impact during children’s most formative years</li></ul>",
